               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel, Homiliary for the feasts of St Michael (fols.
                     4ra-61rb)
 II) ʾAmaḥaḍḍǝnakkǝmu ʾagāʾǝztǝya ʾāb wa-wald wa-manfas qǝddus …
                     “I entrust myself to you my lords, the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit
                     …” (fols. 61rb-64va)
 III) ʾO-za-ʾaṣoruka masqala ʾǝnbālā fǝtḥ … “Oh those
                     who let you carry the cross without justice …” (fols. 64va-65va)</summary>
